        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 15 at 7:26PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 726 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 12
miles southeast of Union, or near Carlisle, moving southwest at 5
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Carlisle, Leeds, and Santuc.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
